The BBC could give up its right to broadcast part of the Wimbledon tennis championship under plans being drawn up by senior executives.

In a move that is likely to dismay many tennis fans, coverage of the event may be shared with BT. 

It would mean some matches would only be available to subscribers of the pay-TV channel.

