According to The Times, senior BBC executives have held talks with BT but have yet to agree to a deal. The corporation has been Wimbledon’s exclusive broadcaster in the UK for nearly 80 years.

It reportedly costs the BBC up to £40million a year to broadcast - a large part of the tournament’s £150million revenue.

By sharing its rights with BT, the corporation would make significant savings. 

It was also reported that the BBC was considering more cost-cutting measures, including commercial partnerships, as it braces itself for further cuts to its licence fee.

